pr_review_comments: [{'comment_id': 943924049, 'comment_body': "@alya should these plan name strings be tagged for translation? Since the landing pages aren't translated, it's a bit unclear to me whether this bit should be.", 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2022, 8, 11, 20, 43, 9, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'timabbott', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 943924500, 'comment_body': 'Is the `br` here necessary, or could be instead set CSS for how it should line-wrap? \r\n\r\nThe `br` hackery will not work if these need to be tagged for translation.', 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2022, 8, 11, 20, 43, 53, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'timabbott', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 943924601, 'comment_body': 'Certainly this one should be tagged for translation. ', 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2022, 8, 11, 20, 44, 3, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'timabbott', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 945110159, 'comment_body': 'Done.', 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2022, 8, 13, 7, 58, 50, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'ganpa3', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 945110177, 'comment_body': 'Removed `br` and used CSS `white-space`.', 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2022, 8, 13, 7, 59, 18, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'ganpa3', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 946246117, 'comment_body': 'What if we make "Zulip Cloud Standard" be a `Upgrade to {plan_name}` variable substitution that is tagged for translation? @alya for thoughts on whether that\'s the right way to do i18n, given that we don\'t translate the plan names anywhere else.', 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2022, 8, 16, 0, 43, 37, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'timabbott', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 951625309, 'comment_body': 'Hm, we should perhaps mark "Upgrade to" for translation, but leave the plan names in English? ', 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2022, 8, 22, 16, 10, 41, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'alya', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 951650338, 'comment_body': 'Good question! As also noted below, maybe we should keep the plan names in English.', 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2022, 8, 22, 16, 35, 39, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'alya', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 960054119, 'comment_body': "That's what I suggested -- with the `{plan_name}` part in a variable, so that folks can still do language-appropriate word order for the part that isn't the plan name.", 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2022, 8, 31, 21, 49, 23, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'timabbott', 'type': 'User'}]

pr_title: confirm_deactivate_user: Provide additional information about user.
pr_review_comments:
[{'comment_id': 910862272, 'comment_body': 'Could we write code for `error()` in case of an error while getting invites?

Everything else LGTM!', 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2022, 6, 30, 10, 25, 21, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'yogesh-sirsat', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 916312465, 'comment_body': "Yeah, or if displaying nothing is appropriate, we should add a comment noting that situation.

(I'm also curious what happens while waiting for this request to return)", 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2022, 7, 7, 22, 0, 31, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'timabbott', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 918649124, 'comment_body': '> Yeah, or if displaying nothing is appropriate, we should add a comment noting that situation.

Done.
> (I'm also curious what happens while waiting for this request to return)

"0 invites" is shown as the default. If the request succeeds, the number of invites is updated.', 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2022, 7, 12, 7, 41, 4, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'ganpa3', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 922573368, 'comment_body': "Let's move this comment after the `success` handler inside the `channel.get` argument block -- that's naturally where one would look for an error handler.", 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2022, 7, 15, 23, 21, 3, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'timabbott', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 922574336, 'comment_body': "This internationalization approach doesn't work -- different languages have different word orders, so one needs to always pass entire sentences to the i18n tools.

Likely we need to move this logic into the template, and just have a 2x2=4 variants of the overall string, if we're trying to explain all these things as a compound sentence (which I generally don't recommend because of the exploding strings that this sort of compound sentence requires). See https://zulip.readthedocs.io/en/latest/translating/internationalization.html", 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2022, 7, 15, 23, 24, 18, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'timabbott', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 922574427, 'comment_body': "This i18n approach doesn't work -- the `0 unexpired invitations` part cannot be translated.", 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2022, 7, 15, 23, 24, 41, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'timabbott', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 927907405, 'comment_body': 'So, this approach is going to result in a brief flash where `0` is displayed regardless of the true value, which seems bad.

What we should do instead is call `confirm_dialog.launch` from the success handler, so that we have all the data when we render the deactivation modal -- and then we can just fill in this value in template rendering, not via JavaScript.', 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2022, 7, 22, 18, 42, 3, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'timabbott', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 927907548, 'comment_body': "I think you can drop this hunk, since we're no longer using the strings involved.", 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2022, 7, 22, 18, 42, 16, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'timabbott', 'type': 'User'}]

pr_title: draft: Fix vertical ellipsis color on hover.
pr_body:
The vertical ellipsis on the "Draft" row in the top left sidebar has a different color on hover than other vertical ellipsis.
This PR fixes that.

## Before
![do](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/58626718/178547902-4744b5a0-e2ae-4915-bd91-2c005787e514.png)
![d1o](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/58626718/178548760-0f4259e3-2ef5-45a7-80b0-ba180bab8841.png)

## After
![dn](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/58626718/178548803-0d7f373e-0520-4935-9473-827df8837fa7.png)
![d1n](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/58626718/178549057-a5a82dcb-f4da-47a3-9f24-ad94e2f92927.png)
